2. Secondly, they say, frugality makes men neglect pietie,
1. Tim. 6.5.6. Mar. 11.15 and the gaine of vngodlinesse makes marchandize of godlinesse; so that buyers and sellers, and spirituall theeues possesse the temple; I meane the labor proper to sixe dayes, makes a sacrilegious vsurpation and horrible profanation of that Rest proper to the Seuenth;
Exod. 20.9.10. and many for feare of seeming Iewes, become Gentiles.
